Sun Staff Walk Out in Sunday Tabloid Closure Protest, Union Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-07T20:44:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/sun-staff-walk-out-in-sunday-tabloid-closure-protest-union-says.html
Journalists at  News Corp. (NWSA) ’s The Sun
newspaper walked out in protest tonight to show support for
colleagues at the company’s Sunday tabloid, the News of the
World, which is being closed, the National Union of Journalists
said in a statement on its  website .  News of the World employees have been told of redundancies
and that they will receive a 90-day payment to cover a legally
required consultation period regarding job cuts, the NUJ said.  A message left on the voicemail of  Daisy Dunlop , a
spokeswoman for News Corp.’s News International U.K. unit,
wasn’t immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 